io.github.jonestimd.swing.window

Class FrameManager<Key extends WindowInfo>

  • java.lang.Object
    • io.github.jonestimd.swing.window.FrameManager<Key>
  • Type Parameters:
    Key - The class defining the window types (typically an enum)
    All Implemented Interfaces:
    WindowEventListener<Key>

    public class FrameManager<Key extends WindowInfo>
extends Object
implements WindowEventListener<Key>
    Manages an application's windows. This class creates window and initializes their menu bar with the Windows and Help menus. This class updates the Windows menu whenever another window is opened or closed. Typically, an instance of this class is registered with a WindowEventPublisher and menu items for opening new windows are created using FrameAction.
